"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5b4b36",
"children":[
"The three main modalities of kidney imaging are ultrasonography, CT, and MRI."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6bb771",
"children":[
"Ultrasonography is used to look for:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ad54c6",
"children":[
"nephrolithiasis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0cecc9",
"children":[
"kidney size and cortical thickness (increased echogenicity implies parenchymal disease)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c2c11a",
"children":[
"renal cysts and tumors"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"63a2c8",
"children":[
"obstruction and hydronephrosis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"2b0956",
"children":[
"bladder size, postvoid residual, and the prostate in bladder outlet obstruction"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"22d666",
"children":[
"CT is used to look for:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b0b1dc",
"children":[
"nephrolithiasis (noncontrast abdominal helical CT)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ced900",
"children":[
"renal tumors and cysts (contrast abdominal CT)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"716e5d",
"children":[
"causes of unexplained nonglomerular hematuria (CT urography)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5840f6",
"children":[
"MRI is used:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1f681f",
"children":[
"to characterize renal masses, cysts, and renal vein thrombosis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"2ea0c4",
"children":[
"to look for renal artery stenosis using ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"magnetic resonance angiography",
"children":[
"MRA"
]
},
" with gadolinium contrast"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
},
